Yes. For Phase 5F, I would keep it tight and make Small Disk the first real non-minimal profile, but only for RHEL 8 right now. That proves the whole profile/template/boot-target chain without accidentally requiring RHEL 7/9/10 small-disk templates.

Phase 5F exact work

You need to do 4 changes.

⸻

1. Update content/profiles/60-small-disk.yml

Change it from placeholder to implemented, and limit it to RHEL 8 for now.

Use this full file:

profile_id: small_disk
title: Small Disk Installs
install_label: Small Disk
menu_target: small_disk
implemented: true
show_in_main_menu: true
uefi: true
bios: true
supported_os:
  - rhel8
kickstart_template: "ks/{{ os_id }}-small-disk.ks.j2"
kernel_args:
  - inst.text
  - nomodeset

The important parts are:

implemented: true
supported_os:
  - rhel8
kickstart_template: "ks/{{ os_id }}-small-disk.ks.j2"

That means it should generate:

/ks/rhel8-small-disk.ks

And boot targets like:

:rhel8_small_disk_uefi
:rhel8_small_disk_bios

⸻

2. Add templates/partials/storage-small-disk.ks.j2

Create this new file:

zerombr
clearpart --all --initlabel
reqpart --add-boot
part / --fstype=xfs --size=8192 --grow

This is the main thing that makes the profile different from minimal.

Your minimal profile uses:

autopart --type=lvm

Small Disk will use a simpler layout with:

reqpart --add-boot
part / --fstype=xfs --size=8192 --grow

That gives you a small-disk-friendly layout and avoids LVM/swap complexity for this first proof.

⸻

3. Add templates/ks/rhel8-small-disk.ks.j2

Create this new file:

#version=RHEL{{ os_major }}
{% include "partials/install-mode-text.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/language-keyboard.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/timezone.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/network-dhcp.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/root-password.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/repo-url.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/storage-small-disk.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/packages-minimal.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/services-basic.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/kdump-enabled.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/post-empty.ks.j2" %}

Notice the only major difference from your minimal template is this line:

{% include "partials/storage-small-disk.ks.j2" %}

instead of:

{% include "partials/storage-default-lvm.ks.j2" %}

⸻

4. Update the built-in small_disk profile in scripts/generate-pxe-content.py

Find the built-in ProfileDefinition for small_disk.

Change it to this:

ProfileDefinition(
    profile_id="small_disk",
    title="Small Disk Installs",
    install_label="Small Disk",
    menu_target="small_disk",
    implemented=True,
    show_in_main_menu=True,
    supported_os=("rhel8",),
    kickstart_template="ks/{{ os_id }}-small-disk.ks.j2",
    kernel_args=("inst.text", "nomodeset"),
),

This matters because if /profiles is ever missing or not mounted, the built-in fallback still behaves like Phase 5F.

⸻

Do not change these yet

Leave these as placeholders:

developer_workstation
security_baseline
security_luks
embedded_edge

Do not implement those yet.

Also, do not add RHEL 7/9/10 small-disk support yet unless you are ready to add and test these too:

templates/ks/rhel7-small-disk.ks.j2
templates/ks/rhel9-small-disk.ks.j2
templates/ks/rhel10-small-disk.ks.j2

For 5F, RHEL 8 only is the cleanest proof because it gives you both UEFI and BIOS behavior.

